WEBVTT

00:00:00.980 --> 00:00:05.620
Is it realistic to believe that you can be a friend with God?

00:00:05.620 --> 00:00:10.900
If until now you've answered no to that question, please consider this.

00:00:10.900 --> 00:00:16.899
The lives of millions of people today prove that friendship with God is possible.

00:00:16.899 --> 00:00:21.699
Their lives prove that we can find a peaceful and meaningful life now,

00:00:21.699 --> 00:00:26.339
as well as hope for a never-lasting and peaceful future.

00:00:26.339 --> 00:00:29.379
If you desire that for yourself and others,

00:00:29.460 --> 00:00:32.020
we urge you to listen to this scriptural talk.

00:00:33.460 --> 00:00:39.140
We emphasize the need to listen, because many people ignore that important question,

00:00:39.140 --> 00:00:42.500
that is, can you be a friend with God?

00:00:43.539 --> 00:00:46.979
Why is it that many put such an important question out of their mind?

00:00:47.700 --> 00:00:52.899
There are a number of reasons. For example, some believe that God is impersonal or

00:00:52.899 --> 00:00:57.539
unknowable, or that He does not exist and that He's not interested in humans.

00:00:58.340 --> 00:01:03.939
They are taught that God is a mystery, and that He is cruel, harsh, and demanding.

00:01:05.140 --> 00:01:10.500
Many religious leaders claim that God will punish bad people forever in a place of torment.

00:01:11.379 --> 00:01:14.500
Do you feel drawn into friendship with a God like that?

00:01:15.379 --> 00:01:17.459
Who in their right mind would?

00:01:18.659 --> 00:01:23.299
Still other people, after seeing all of the injustice and suffering in the world,

00:01:23.299 --> 00:01:27.859
have concluded that God must be dead, or that He never existed at all.

00:01:28.980 --> 00:01:33.700
And then there are those who believe that they have done too many bad things in their life to

00:01:33.700 --> 00:01:41.140
ever be a friend of God. Do any of those causes for doubt or concern apply to you?

00:01:42.019 --> 00:01:48.500
If so, please listen carefully to the following four key points that may help you to see that

00:01:48.500 --> 00:01:52.980
friendship with God is truly possible, we will then develop each one.

00:01:54.019 --> 00:02:01.620
First, we'll look at how sin separates us from God. Second, we'll look at how God has taken

00:02:01.620 --> 00:02:07.379
the initiative to heal the breach and bring obedient humans back into friendship with Him.

00:02:08.580 --> 00:02:14.659
Then, we'll examine what we can do to become God's friend in an everlasting way.

00:02:15.379 --> 00:02:21.379
And finally, we will consider how friendship with God brings peace now and in the future.

00:02:22.419 --> 00:02:30.180
So, for our first point, what is it that separates us from God in a word sin?

00:02:31.379 --> 00:02:40.500
Why does sin separate us? Because the true God is holy, he's pure, and his conduct is perfect.

00:02:40.500 --> 00:02:48.099
He does not have a trace of sin, he's clean and the highest sense. No human can be holy to that degree,

00:02:48.819 --> 00:02:56.900
not even close. To illustrate, consider the words human and imperfect. They go together, don't they?

00:02:56.900 --> 00:03:02.500
You cannot fully describe humans without mentioning imperfection. It's just a part of us,

00:03:02.979 --> 00:03:06.740
and human history shows this to be sadly and painfully true.

00:03:07.699 --> 00:03:14.020
So then, our sins or imperfections create a barrier between us and God.

00:03:14.900 --> 00:03:22.259
This separation is described at Isaiah chapter 59 and verse 2 where we are told in part.

00:03:23.860 --> 00:03:30.979
Your own errors have separated you from your God. Your sins have made him hide his face from you.

00:03:31.620 --> 00:03:40.580
Separated from God, it says, we were born into this state, but God did not create us to be sinful.

00:03:40.580 --> 00:03:47.780
Our sins are not his fault. The first humans, Adam and Eve, were created perfect,

00:03:47.780 --> 00:03:54.580
but they proved to be ungrateful and selfish, and they rejected God's friendship.

00:03:55.379 --> 00:04:00.979
They destroyed their peace with God by sinning against him, and they became his enemies.

00:04:01.860 --> 00:04:09.460
Adam then passed sin on to his descendants as well as death. We read about this terrible inheritance

00:04:09.460 --> 00:04:19.379
at Romans chapter 5 and verse 12. In this verse, the Apostle Paul summarizes why our inherited

00:04:19.379 --> 00:04:26.980
sinful condition leads to death. He wrote, that is why just as through one man sin entered into

00:04:26.980 --> 00:04:35.779
the world and death through sin, and so death spread to all men because they had all sinned.

00:04:37.300 --> 00:04:48.019
Death spread to all men. This pandemic of sin has a 100% infection rate and a 100% mortality rate.

00:04:48.579 --> 00:04:55.379
No human can escape it. As Paul said, death spread because they had all sinned.

00:04:56.660 --> 00:05:03.540
On our own, we cannot correct our sinful state. It's as if we have fallen into a deep pit with

00:05:03.540 --> 00:05:11.060
seemingly no way out. But are we left without hope? No. In fact, although God views some people as

00:05:11.060 --> 00:05:19.060
his enemies, he treats others as his friends. For example, regarding the man Abraham, the Bible book

00:05:19.060 --> 00:05:26.819
of James says in chapter 2 and verse 23, that Abraham put faith in Jehovah, and it was counted to

00:05:26.819 --> 00:05:36.660
him as righteousness, and he came to be called Jehovah's Friend. Abraham was as imperfect as we are,

00:05:37.300 --> 00:05:44.019
but he came to be called God's Friend. What has God done to make it possible for humans to gain

00:05:44.019 --> 00:05:52.420
his favor and blessing? Simply put, our Creator has taken the initiative. He has taken steps to

00:05:52.420 --> 00:05:58.339
heal the breach that was caused by sin and to eliminate the separation between us and him.

00:05:59.300 --> 00:06:06.420
How has he done this? First, the Holy Scriptures tell us that God desires for us to come to know him,

00:06:07.060 --> 00:06:15.220
and to be at peace with him. In fact, he appeals to us to do this. In the Bible book of Acts chapter 17

00:06:15.220 --> 00:06:23.060
and verse 27, we are told that God wants us to sincerely seek him, and that if we do, we will find

00:06:23.060 --> 00:06:31.220
that he's not far off from each one of us. Next, and very important, God took the initiative to make

00:06:31.459 --> 00:06:38.339
this possible by providing the sacrifice of his son Jesus in order to redeem us from sin.

00:06:39.379 --> 00:06:47.379
That was an unparalleled act of love. As we now read first John chapter 4 and verse 10,

00:06:48.660 --> 00:06:55.060
please think about what it says regarding this matchless act of love on God's part,

00:06:55.060 --> 00:07:01.060
and so that we may never forget that God took the initiative to heal the breach, so to speak.

00:07:01.540 --> 00:07:07.939
First, John 4, 10 says, the love is in this respect, not that we have loved God,

00:07:08.579 --> 00:07:16.420
but that he loved us and sent his son as a propitiatory sacrifice for our sins.

00:07:17.620 --> 00:07:27.060
What did God do? God loved us, it says, and he sent his son. This sacrifice that God provided by

00:07:27.139 --> 00:07:33.540
means of his son is called propitiatory because it can atone for our sins, and here is how it can

00:07:33.540 --> 00:07:42.660
do so. What Jesus gave in sacrifice for us was equal to what Adam lost for us, that is a perfect

00:07:42.660 --> 00:07:50.180
human life. Adam exchanged his perfect life for death by his rebellion against God.

00:07:50.980 --> 00:07:57.939
As mentioned earlier, Adam then passed sin onto his descendants, and he placed this on a path

00:07:57.939 --> 00:08:04.579
outside of God's friendship. On the other hand, the death of Jesus allowed for a ransom,

00:08:04.579 --> 00:08:10.180
or a means to satisfy God's justice so that we could receive back what Adam lost for us.

00:08:11.139 --> 00:08:18.339
That undeserved gift from God was given a great cost, clearly our creator wants us to come to know

00:08:19.060 --> 00:08:26.339
and to enjoy a beautiful friendship with him. We should be very grateful that God took the necessary

00:08:26.339 --> 00:08:35.220
step to close the gap and provide a way for us to become his friend. The next step involves

00:08:35.220 --> 00:08:42.980
each of us, what is required of us, humility. We must be humble enough to accept God's gift.

00:08:43.620 --> 00:08:50.580
If we are humble, we'll see our need for God's mercy, and we'll then do our part to show

00:08:50.580 --> 00:08:58.500
appreciation. The Bible book of Acts chapter 3 in verse 19 tells us that this involves repenting

00:08:58.500 --> 00:09:05.059
and turning around. In other words, to receive God's gift, which includes his mercy,

00:09:05.620 --> 00:09:12.019
we must adjust our thinking by repenting and then turn around by adjusting our conduct in

00:09:12.019 --> 00:09:18.179
course in life wherever necessary. The opportunity to do this is open to all people.

00:09:18.820 --> 00:09:24.500
As our creator, God is not partial in his mercy, and in the friendship he offers.

00:09:25.059 --> 00:09:31.940
He has kindly put everything in place for us. All we must do is be grateful and humble,

00:09:31.940 --> 00:09:38.980
and then take the next step. That step involves accepting Jesus and his teachings.

00:09:39.779 --> 00:09:45.700
God requires that we follow the example of his son. How closely must we do so?

00:09:46.500 --> 00:09:50.100
At John chapter 14 and verse 6, Jesus explained,

00:09:50.980 --> 00:10:00.259
I am the way and the truth and the life. No one comes to the Father except through me. No one.

00:10:01.379 --> 00:10:07.220
So then to come into God's friendship, we must follow his son as true Christians.

